The Position

The Traffic team provides infrastructure to enable fast and reliable access to Twitter for anyone, anywhere, on any network. Our mission of shaping the next generation of Twitter traffic control directly impacts the lives of our users, their trust in our platform, and the success of our business. Through software and protocols, traffic steering, global load balancing, and regional content caching and distribution, we remove the barriers that prevent people from participating in the public conversation.

As a Senior Software Engineer, you will collaborate with highly motivated and wonderful software engineers, data scientists, network architects, and client engineers. You will lead and support innovative solutions to sophisticated and modern engineering challenges, to enhance Twitter’s Edge initiatives. As part of the team, you will learn, teach, grow, and help bring Twitter closer to our users. You will make critical decisions, write designs and code that drives user... growth and satisfaction through reliability and performance improvements.

What You’ll Do:
• Contribute to the team’s vision and articulate strategies to have fundamental impact at our massive scale;
• Ideate and drive innovative projects that will improve user experience;
• Provide strong leadership within your very own problem space, through data-driven decisions, robust software designs, and effective delegation;
• Actively engage with cross-functional teams such as network specialists, data scientists, or client engineers to identify and iterate on game-changing opportunities;
• Build and maintain high-performance, fault-tolerant and scalable distributed systems;
• Establish and uphold best engineering practices through thorough code and design reviews and improved processes and tools;
• Groom junior engineers through mentoring and delegation;
• Diagnose and solve complex problems in distributed systems, and develop solutions that have a significant impact at Twitter’s massive scale;
• Drive a culture of trust, respect and inclusion within your team.

Who You Are:
• You are excited about building massively scalable solutions and top tier services for worldwide impact;
• You want to iterate quickly and safely on high scale systems;
• You love to collaborate, mentor, and learn with a great team;
• Passionate about finding elegant solutions to complex technical problems;
• Want to challenge yourself, and to work with the best engineers in the industry;
• You are always looking for opportunities to grow and learn;
• You enjoy working both collaboratively and independently.

Qualifications
• At least 4 years of software development experience, preferably with backend infrastructure, distributed systems and/or performance analysis;
• Proven experience with software engineering standard methodologies for iterative development, testing, code reuse, etc…;
• Strong bias to action, creative problem solving attitude, and proactive communication;
• Strong design and architecture skills;
• Excellent written and verbal communication skills;
• Experience in iOS or Web development is a plus.

Company Description

Twitter serves the public conversation because conversation is a force for good in the world. The opportunity to help the world connect, debate, learn, and solve problems is what draws us to careers at Twitter, and it’s what keeps us here
